 which contains the eigenvalues:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard


\begin_inset Formula \[ \textbf{V} = \textbf{P}^{-1} \mbox{\boldmath$\Lambda$} \textbf{P} \]
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

The columns of 
\begin_inset Formula $\textbf{P}$
\end_inset

 are our principal components. We order them by the amount of variance in the data set they are able to accommodate so that our first component accounts for the largest amount of variance.
\end_layout

